So, to limit acceleration, I would initialize a slew rate limiter and change it to something like:

    s_Swerve.drive(
        new Translation2d(translationVal, strafeVal).times(Constants.Swerve.maxSpeed),
        accelerationLimiter.calculate(rotationVal)* Constants.Swerve.maxAngularVelocity,
        !robotCentricSup.getAsBoolean(),
        true);

Quick question about slew rate limiter, I was reading the wpilib documentation on the slew rate limiter and it gave this example for initializing it:

// Creates a SlewRateLimiter that limits the rate of change of the signal to 0.5 units per second
SlewRateLimiter filter = new SlewRateLimiter(0.5);

What does it mean by limiting the rate of change of the signal, is a lower number just going to mean a slower acceleration or something?
